{
  "stem": "10768.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Or did you experience any anti-Semitism before the war?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I really personally didn't feel it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Maybe it was because of my Polish name, also because my childhood was spent with my paternal grandfather, and I spoke a very good Polish.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My Polish didn't have the Jewish accent.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So unless-- of course, there was no secret.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everybody knew that I was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In our schools, in the public schools, even though the schools were open on Saturday and they were teaching on Saturday subjects-- but the teachers-- since we had-- 80% of the students were Jewish, so the teachers usually gave the secondary subjects like gym, arts and crafts.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "These, these subjects were taught on Saturday.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we were compelled to take the guidelines from other students and make it up on our own.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the next week or in the middle of the week if you had a art class, we had to bring our, our projects prepared.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The schools, the schools really were, I would say, on a very high level.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Starting from the second grade, since we had quite large Ukrainian population in the outskirts of the city, we were taught the, the Ukrainian alphabet, which is also the same alphabet as in, as was used in Russia.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were taught from second grade on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "On the fifth grade, we were taught German.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "At the beginning, they even taught the Gothic, which was later abandoned.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we were taught German.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And even towards the end-- it was a seventh-grade school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But towards the end, it was already like two or three years in, let's say, a high school.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was like a junior high school in United States.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I would presume so.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I don't know exactly how the curriculum here is.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
